### 3. `docs/design-anti-patterns.md` — amend AP-066

Find the existing AP-066 entry (in the **Navigation & Menus** category) and replace it with the amended version that includes this new canonical example:

```markdown
<a id="ap-066"></a>
## AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text

**Status: ACTIVE**

**Trigger:** A nav logo or site identity line sits inside a flex container with `flex-shrink: 0` on the logo item, but without `min-width: max-content`. The text wraps to two lines when the viewport is squeezed.

**Why it's wrong:** `flex-shrink: 0` stops *proportional* shrinkage during the flex distribution pass — it says "don't take space away from this item relative to siblings." It does **not** set an absolute minimum floor. When the flex container's available space drops below the sum of all children's intrinsic widths, the browser's layout engine can still collapse items that lack an explicit `min-width`. The logo wraps because it has no hard floor, not because `flex-shrink` was missing.

The compound structure makes this worse: the logo is typically an `inline-flex` wrapper containing an icon (`display: inline-block`) and text. `white-space: nowrap` on the text child prevents *internal* line-breaks, but does not stop the flex algorithm from shrinking the wrapper's box width below the text's rendered extent.

**Identity text is never the yield point.** The site name, wordmark, or core identity line must be structurally immovable at all viewport widths. Supporting content (taglines, blurbs, secondary nav links) is the designated yield surface.

**Correct alternative:**

```css
/* The logo item — both properties are required */
.logo {
  flex-shrink: 0;           /* stops proportional shrink */
  min-width: max-content;   /* hard floor: cannot collapse below intrinsic width */
}

/* The logo text child — prevents internal wrapping */
.logoText {
  white-space: nowrap;
}

/* The yield-side sibling — absorbs all squeeze */
.links {
  min-width: 0;             /* overrides flex default min-width: auto */
}

/* The parent container — make the nowrap guarantee explicit */
.navInner {
  flex-wrap: nowrap;
}
```

**Yield hierarchy for horizontal nav bars:**

| Priority | Element | CSS |
|----------|---------|-----|
| Never yields | Logo / wordmark | `flex-shrink: 0` + `min-width: max-content` |
| Yields last | Nav links | `flex-shrink: 0` (or explicit `min-width`) |
| Designated yield | Tagline / blurb | `min-width: 0` on container, content wraps |

**Canonical implementation:** `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss` — `.logo`, `.logoText`, `.links`, `.navInner`.

**See:** FB-146, FB-150 (same pattern in experience column — company names must never wrap).
```

